Executive Profile
Sidney   Lapidus J.D.Managing Director and Senior Advisor, Warburg Pincus LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 8 Board Members in 8 different organizations across 8 different industries.See Board Relationships79--
Background

		Mr. Sidney Lapidus, also known as Sid, J.D. serves as the President and Chairman of United Neighborhood Houses. Mr. Lapidus was the Managing Director and Senior Advisor of Warburg Pincus LLC. Mr. Lapidus was a Senior Partner at Warburg Pincus from 1967 to 2007. He has been a Director of Four Media Company, LLC since 2002; Information Holdings Inc. since December 1996; Radio Unica Communications Corp. since September 1998 and Radio Unica Corp. since September 1998. He ... has been a Director of Lennar Corp. since April 1997 and its Lead Director since 2005. He has been an Independent Director of Knoll, Inc. since February 1996. Mr. Lapidus serves on the Board of Directors of Caribiner International, Grubb & Ellis Company, Journal Register Company as well as several privately held companies. He has been an affiliate of the Purchasers since 1974. He has been associated with EMW LLC or its predecessor since 1967. Mr. Lapidus serves as a Trustee of the New York University School of Medicine Foundation Board and a Councilor and Vice Chairman of the American Antiquarian Society. He served as a Director at The Neiman Marcus Group LLC. He earned a B.A. degree in American History at Princeton University and a J.D. degree from Columbia University Law School.Read Full Background




