epartment different so you can shop with confidence. Unlike fashion jewelry, which is made from lower-quality materials like plastic and stainless steel, fine jewelry is meant to last a lifetime. It may incorporate some trendy design elements, but ultimately, fine jewelry is built to stand the test of time thanks to its use of high-quality materials and expert construction. This is what makes fine jewelry such a great choice for important gifts; it's an investment in quality that symbolizes love, admiration, respect or accomplishment with the use of symbolic precious metals and gemstones that signify value and longevity. engagement rings are perhaps the most famous example of fine jewelry, but there are many other types of jewelry pieces in this category.GemstonesMany fine jewelry pieces use gemstones like diamond, cubic zirconia, pearl, ruby, sapphire and emerald to add color and sparkle to rings, earrings, necklaces and bracelets. Some of Walmart's fine jewelry items use simulated gemstones to offer a more affordable option for those who want to maintain the look and feel of fine jewelry on any budget. These simulated gemstones have a similar appearance but have a different molecular structure from the genuine gemstone they're designed to copy. Look for words like "created" or "simulated" as you shop our Fine Jewelry department to focus on faux gemstones for a beautiful alternative to the genuine article.MetalsStrong, attractive metals like gold, silver, titanium and tungsten are commonly found in the Fine Jewelry department. These metals are durable, shiny, and comfortable to wear, and in the case of gold and silver, they've been used to make fine jewelry for centuries. Gold comes in different purity grades and colors, and understanding the difference between these options will make it easiest to find the jewelry style you want. Gold is actually a very soft metal, so pure gold, also known as 24 karat (24k) gold, isn't the strongest type of gold available. Eighteen karat gold is a common purity grade used in fine jewelry; it uses 75 percent gold with a few other metals mixed in to make it stronger and less prone to bending or scratching. Traditional yellow gold is what most people think of when they think of gold, but you can also find white gold, which is a silvery color, and rose gold, which is mixed with copper to produce a warm pinkish-orange shade that can function as an accent color or as the primary metal for a piece of fine jewelry.Fine jewelry stylesMany fine jewelry pieces have an ornate style with embellishments and accent stones to add more flash and make the piece more noticeable. You can find different styles and narrow down your options by shopping through the subcategories in our Fine Jewelry department.Men's fine jewelryWalmart's Fine Jewelry department includes styles designed specifically for men. These jewelry pieces are larger and heavier than jewelry designs for women, and they're often less ornate. From class rings and other commemorative jewelry styles to simple gold chains and rings with stones set into the band, there's something for every man in this section.Women's fine jewelryWomen's fine jewelry styles are often delicate, but they can be quite ornate and flashy. Details such as chain width for necklaces and bracelets or band thickness for rings are often lighter and less chunky than they're for comparable men's jewelry styles, making women's fine jewelry pieces more feminine. These details are also more comfortable and stylish for a smaller hand, wrist or neck.Religious and keepsake jewelryAs high-quality jewelry that's designed to be worn regularly, fine jewelry can be a highly personal expression of values. Religious and keepsake jewelry items include both religious symbols and symbolic jewelry that commemorates family and professional accomplishments. There are religious and keepsake jewelry items in both men's and women's fine jewelry styles, allowing you to purchase religious or family jewelry for everyone you love. From crosses to hearts representing each child in a family, this style of fine jewelry can be very meaningful to the person who wears it.Show moreElectrode, Comp-115863236, DC-prod-dal1, ENV-prod-a, PROF-PROD, VER-1.15.0, SHA-06ca1a9068b558bd33bd1add57a0b13a52090f9f, CID-


